---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - Justin Doone"
  description="Digital marketing manager at Evolve ETFs. Past work at Greybrook Realty Partners and Clifton Blake, with consulting for consumer brands."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12 pt-20 md:pt-32 pb-16">
    <img
      src="/images/profile.jpg"
      alt="Justin Doone"
      width="200"
      height="200"
      class="hero-line w-36 h-36 md:w-44 md:h-44 rounded-full object-cover mb-10 ring-1 ring-rule"
      data-line="0"
    />
    <p class="hero-line eyebrow mb-8" data-line="0">About</p>
    <h1 class="hero-line heading-display text-5xl md:text-7xl text-ink mb-10 leading-[0.95]" data-line="1">
      I do marketing for firms with something complicated to sell.
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-line text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-6" data-line="2">
      Toronto-based. Currently running digital marketing at Evolve ETFs.
    </p>
    <p class="hero-line text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed" data-line="3">
      Before Evolve: <strong class="text-ink font-medium">Greybrook Realty Partners</strong> and <strong class="text-ink font-medium">Clifton Blake</strong>, plus some consumer brand consulting in the gaps.
    </p>
    <p class="hero-line text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mt-6" data-line="4">
      The average day is split between writing copy, working through compliance edits, and arguing with a chart that says something I don't believe. The actual job lives across that whole spectrum, not just at the strategy meeting.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW I WORK -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12 py-16 rule-top" data-reveal>
    <p class="eyebrow mb-8">How I work</p>
    <div class="space-y-8 text-ink-soft leading-relaxed text-lg">
      <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
        Before I design anything I want to know two things: who we're trying to reach and what they need to believe by the end of it. Skip that step and the rest of the campaign turns into fix-it-in-execution work, which costs about three times what figuring it out up front would have.
      </p>
      <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
        I work from one story and bend it across whatever channels we're using. Most channel plans end up as nine slightly different versions of the same idea. That's a content calendar with strategy ambitions, not actually a strategy.
      </p>
      <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="3">
        I do the measurement work myself. SQL, dashboards, attribution arguments at 11 PM with someone who's sure their channel deserves more credit. If I can't tell reach and revenue apart after a campaign, I haven't done my half of the job.
      </p>
      <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="4">
        In financial services and other regulated rooms, the best work is the work that clears compliance on the first read. I write to the line, not over it. The difference between launching this quarter and launching whenever legal gets to it is usually one careful first draft.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA (dark) -->
  <section class="dark-section relative py-24 md:py-32 mt-20" data-reveal>
    <div class="hero-orb" style="top: 0%; right: -10%; opacity: 0.3;"></div>
    <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 lg:px-12">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-6">Get in touch</p>
      <h2 class="heading-display text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-8" style="color: var(--color-on-dark);">
        If you have something complicated to sell, I can probably help.
      </h2>
      <a
        href="mailto:justindoone@gmail.com"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-accent text-paper px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-accent-warm transition-colors"
      >
        justindoone@gmail.com
        <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
